    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-15T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-15T11:00:00-05:00" n="893"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d893">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2361A/8–1544: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-15T19:00:00+03:00"
                            >August 15, 1944—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11:59 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2999. Soviet military authorities have furnished Military Mission with names of
                    34 additional United States aviators who are understood <pb facs="0994" n="984"
                        xml:id="pg_984"/> to have landed near Petropavlovsk several weeks ago.
                    Further particulars are being awaited. It is not clear whether these were Army,
                    Navy or Marine planes.</p>
                <p>Foregoing is for your<note n="94" xml:id="d893fn1">The Consul General at
                        Vladivostok, Angus Ivan Ward, is here intended.</note> information only but
                    you should of course report promptly any information you may receive.</p>
                <p>Sent to Vladivostok, repeated to Department as No. 2999 August 15, 7 p.m.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
